    <div class=header>
        <h2>What is an Avalanche</h2>
    </div>

    <div class=content>
        <p>An avalanche is a sudden and massive flow of snow, ice,
            and debris down a mountainside, triggered by various
            disturbances such as heavy snowfall, rapid temperature changes, or human activity.
            These snow masses can travel at incredible speeds, sweeping through entire valleys and causing
            extensive destruction in their path. The average speed of an avalanche is around 80 mph.
            The deadliest avalanche occurred in 1970 in Peru, where it claimed thousands of lives.
            The term "avalanche" comes from the French word "avalanche," which means "descent" or "fall."</p>
    </div>

